The paper discusses the use of deep learning algorithms, specifically LSTM, for forecasting time series data in economics and finance. This topic falls under the intersection of computer science and economics/finance, making it likely to be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), social and information networks (cs.SI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
